A. aramburui exhibits bony hooks on all fins of mature males. This dimorphic character has also been reported in several species that have been recently described from the Paranoplatensean basin:
A. chico Casciotta & Almiron
;
A. hermosus Miquelarena, Protogino & Lopez
;
A. ojiara Azpelicueta & Garcia
;
A. pynandi Casciotta, Almiron , Bechara, Roux & Ruiz Diaz
;
A. troya Azpelicueta, Casciotta & Almiron
;
A. leonidas Azpelicueta, Casciotta & Almiron
(without bony hooks on dorsal fin); and A. tumbayaensis Miquelarena & Menni (without bony hooks on pectoral fin). The new species differs from A.chico , A. leonidas , A. ojiara , A. pynandi , A. troya , and A. tumbayaensis by having a coloration pattern that includes a single humeral spot (vs. two humeral spots). A. aramburui shares with A. hermosus the presence of a single humeral spot, which, however, differs in shape (rounded vs. Y-shaped).
